Single File Programming Question
Detect Start of Cycle in Customer Service 



A customer service system in Chennai maintains a linked list of service requests. Due to a software bug, some requests form a loop (cycle) — meaning after a certain request, the system keeps repeating the same sequence.



Your task is to:

detect if a cycle exists
if yes → find the exact node where the cycle begins
if no → return -1
Input format :
First line: integer n — number of nodes
Second line: n space-separated integers (node values)
Third line: integer pos — index where tail connects -1 → no cycle otherwise → 0-based index of cycle start
Output format :
Print the value of node where cycle begins
If no cycle exists → print -1
Code constraints :
0 <= n <= 10^4
-10^5 <= node.val <= 10^5
pos is -1 or valid index
Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
4
3 2 0 -4
1
Output 1 :
2
Input 2 :
2
1 2
0
Output 2 :
1
Note :
The program will be evaluated only after the “Submit Code” is clicked.
Extra spaces and new line characters in the program output will result in the failure of the test case.
